Earlier this month Wiseman, another U.S. astronaut Steve Swanson, and German astronaut Alexander Gerst, showed off their microgravity football skills by performing impressive bicycle kicks, spins and somersaults while kicking a ball.

Wiseman, from Baltimore, Maryland, has taken over the mantle of incredible ISS social media posts from Commander Chris Hadfield, who posted on Twitter, Facebook and Tumblr to a large following of people around the world.

Hadfield, a keen musician, was even filmed performing David Bowie's Space Oddity in low gravity and performed a duet with Canadian band Barenaked Ladies via a video feed from space.

