Reid Wiseman, of Baltimore, Maryland, arrived at the space station on May 28 as part of the Expedition 40/41 crew.

They are scheduled to spend the next several months living and working in space until they return to Earth in November 2014.

Before takeoff, Wiseman's wife Carroll and their two daughters bid him an emotional goodbye, knowing they won't see him until November.

